# BMC Calculadora — CODEOWNERS
#
# Required reviewer mapping for GitHub PRs. GitHub's CODEOWNERS resolution
# is **order-dependent**: the LAST matching pattern in this file takes
# precedence (not the most specific). When editing, keep the catch-all
# default at the top and put more-specific path rules below so they
# correctly override the default for those paths.
#
# Default — single CODEOWNER until a second human collaborator is added.
* @matiasportugau-ui

# ─── Security-sensitive paths ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# These paths handle authentication, authorization, customer PII, prompt
# injection surface, or third-party write surfaces (Sheets, WhatsApp, GCS).
# Listed individually below so a future second reviewer can be added
# (e.g. `@bmc-security` or a named GitHub username) WITHOUT touching the
# default catch-all rule above. Until a second collaborator exists, these
# rules continue to map to @matiasportugau-ui — same as today, but now the
# structural gate is in place for a one-line update later.
#
# How to add a second reviewer once available:
#   1. Add the username/team to the right of @matiasportugau-ui on each
#      line below (CODEOWNERS uses space-separated owners — ALL listed
#      owners are requested as reviewers; ANY one of them can approve).
#   2. (Optional, stricter) Combine with branch protection rule
#      "Require review from Code Owners" + "Require approval from someone
#      other than the last pusher" for true 2-person rule on these paths.

# Auth + authorization core
# Note: list specific files rather than the whole /server/middleware/
# directory so future non-auth middleware doesn't inherit a stricter
